title: Love Island Australia: Vanessa Sierra's cosmetic transformation
text:
Never-before-seen photos of Love Island Australia star Vanessa Sierra reveal how she seemingly transformed her appearance before the show.

In throwback snaps from her teenage years, the 24-year-old businesswoman looks completely different and far less glamorous than today.

Several photos show her with a larger nose and noticeably thinner lips, which suggests she may have undergone cosmetic enhancements.

My, how you've changed! Never-before-seen photos of Love Island Australia star Vanessa Sierra reveal how she completely transformed her appearance before the show. Pictured left: Vanessa as a teenager, and right: in a recent modelling photo

The changing shape of Vanessa's nose could be the result of rhinoplasty surgery.

Her nose looks far slimmer and more refined today, something which is particularly evident in her modelling photos and Instagram selfies.

Meanwhile, her upper lip appears to have doubled in size in recent years, possibly due to non-surgical lip fillers, such as Juvéderm.

Somebody's popular! Vanessa caused a stir on the first episode of Love Island Australia, coupling up with three different men. Pictured on the show with Matthew Zukowski

Did she go under the knife? Several throwback photos show Vanessa with a larger nose and thinner lips (left), which suggests she may have undergone cosmetic enhancements. Pictured right: Vanessa on Love Island

Hmm! The changing shape of Vanessa's nose could be the result of rhinoplasty surgery

Despite her young age, Vanessa may have also undergone Botox to prevent wrinkles from forming on her forehead.

Her eyebrows appear noticeably arched in some photos, which is a tell-tale sign of the cosmetic procedure.

On Monday's episode of Love Island Australia, Vanessa was first chosen by heavily-tattooed Adam Farrugia, but the pairing didn't last.

Changes: Vanessa's nose looks far slimmer and more refined today, something which is particularly evident in her modelling photos and Instagram selfies (right)

She then stepped forward to couple up with handsome DJ Sam Withers.

When this didn't work out, she was picked out by professional wrestler and model Matthew Zukowski.

Love Island Australia continues Tuesday at 8:30pm on Channel Nine
